cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

The paper focuses on the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for visual perception tasks in automated driving, which is a combination of computer vision and robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the computational efficiency and optimization techniques, which suggests a focus on robotics and machine learning, respectively. Hence, cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a joint multi-task network design, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
